StartLocation: Location of the start of the trace.
LaunchVelocity: Initial launch velocity at the start of the trace.
bTraceWithCollision: Whether to trace along the path looking for blocking collision and stopping at the first hit.
ProjectileRadius: Projectile radius, used when tracing for collision. If <= 0, a line trace is used instead.
MaxSimTime: Maximum simulation time for the virtual projectile.
bTraceWithChannel: Whether or not to use TraceChannel, if tracing with collision.
TraceChannel: Trace channel to use, if tracing with collision.
ObjectTypes: Object type to use, if tracing with collision.
ActorsToIgnore: Actors to ignore when tracing with collision.
SimFrequency: Determines size of each sub-step in the simulation (chopping up MaxSimTime). Recommended between 10 to 30 depending on desired quality versus performance.
OverrideGravityZ: Optional override of Gravity (if 0, uses WorldGravityZ).
DrawDebugTime: Duration of debug lines (only relevant for DrawDebugType::Duration)
bTraceComplex: Trace against complex collision (triangles rather than simple primitives) if tracing with collision.
